** UX AT DYE & DURHAM **

We are a growing team spanning across multiple regions, we are passionate
about advocating for our users, using research and insights to help make our
design decisions. Designers at Dye & Durham are more than pixel pushers, we
are:

  * Highly collaborative working closely with Product, engineering, sales and marketing to deliver great products for our users internally and externally 
  * Always thinking about the bigger picture and the context that are users are in 
  * Passionate about career growth, diversity and being inclusive 
  * Always bringing an attitude of good vibes, honesty and a low ego to work 

** WHAT WILL YOU DO? **

We are looking for a driven Senior Product Designer to joining our growing
design team. You will be a champion of our users needs, understanding their
challenges and working closely with Product and Engineering to create a high-
quality and consistent user experience across your domain.

  * Take ownership of end-to-end UX processes and champion our users needs with your team 
  * Form a deep understanding of our users needs informed by UX research and insights 
  * Use data and insights to drive design decisions 
  * Collaborate closely with Product and Engineering throughout the design process to identify new opportunities to improve our products 
  * Plan and conduct UX research to inform design and product decisions 
  * Facilitate design workshops with multidisciplinary teams across the business 
  * Craft design solutions that work for the user and meet business goals 
  * Ensure our journeys meet the user needs whilst being consistent across our products 
  * Communicate and present various stages of design development to team members and other business partners. 

** WHAT DO YOU NEED TO BE CONSIDERED? **

  * Qualification or experience in Interaction Design, Computer Interaction, Behavioural Psychology, or another related field 
  * Expertise in user research, end-to-end design process, conceptualisation, UI prototyping, user testing, and implementation 
  * Experience in service design and systems thinking. You are able to think holistically across all touchpoints 
  * Expertise in using a range of quantitative and qualitative research methods, to measure design impact. 
  * Ability to work closely with Product, Engineering, and other designers to deliver product strategy and meet business goals 
  * Proficiency in Figma, Miro and other related tools 
  * Able to build strong working relations with peers 
  * Well organised and pragmatic problem solver who is motivated to create great user experiences 
  * 5 days in office 

